Citation.sTitle: Experimental (vapour + liquid) equilibrium data of (methanol + water), (water + glycerol) and (methanol + glycerol) systems at atmospheric and sub-atmospheric pressures
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental (vapour + liquid) equilibrium results for the binary systems, (methanol + water) at the local atmospheric pressure of 95.3 kPa and at sub-atmospheric pressures of (15.19, 29.38, 42.66, 56.03, and 67.38) kPa, (water + glycerol) system at pressures (14.19, 29.38, 41.54, 54.72, 63.84, and 95.3) kPa and the (methanol + glycerol) system at pressures (32.02 and 45.3) kPa were obtained over the entire composition range using a Swietoslawski-type ebulliometer. The relationship of the liquid composition (x1) as a function of temperature (T) was found to be well represented by the Wilson model. Computed vapour phase mole fractions, activity coefficients and the measured values along with optimum Wilson parameters are presented.
